- if @name.present?
  - content_for(:page_title, ("Find out #{@name}'s martian birthday"))
  - content_for(:page_description, ("#{@name}'s Martian birthday is on #{@m_month} #{@m_date}, #{@m_year}"))
- else
  - content_for(:page_title, ("Find out Martian birthday on #{@earth_dob}"))
  - content_for(:page_description, ("Martian date equivalent to Earth's #{@earth_dob} is #{@m_month} #{@m_date}, #{@m_year}"))
- content_for(:image, (request.scheme + '://' + request.host + @image_location if @image_location))
- content_for(:page_url, (request.url if request.url))

.container-fluid
  .card.d-flex.justify-content-center.align-items-center.mt-3
    .card-body.p-5
      .row
        .col-sm-8.col-xs-12
          .earth.d-flex.align-items-center
            = image_tag 'noun_Earth_231504.svg', width: '50px', class: 'mr-2', alt: 'Earth by Ariel Kotzer from the Noun Project'
            p
              | Birthdate on Earth&nbsp;
              span.font-weight-bold #{@earth_dob}
          .mars.d-flex.align-items-center
            = image_tag 'noun_Mars_288064.svg', width: '45px', class: 'mr-2', alt: 'Mars by lastspark from the Noun Project'
            p
              | #{@name && @name.length > 0 ? "#{@name.capitalize}'s" : 'Your'} Martian birthday is&nbsp;
              span.font-weight-bold #{@m_month} #{@m_date}, #{@m_year} MCE
          br
          p
            span.font-weight-bold  What does this mean?
            |&nbsp;
            span Well, remember that Martian #{@month_name} is the 21st of the 24 months in the MCE calendar. It has nothing to do with "our" #{@month_name}! In fact, the #{@month}th is the last day of the month. And the year #{@mrtn_year} sounds medieval tol us! But Mars takes  nearly twice as long to orbit the sun. Think of it this way: while the Earth orbited the sun #{@earth_year} times, Mars only orbited #{@mrtn_year} times.
          p If you want to see how the tow planets were positioned on the day you were born, checkout the image above.
          P Famouse people sharing you Martilan birthday
        .col-sm-4.col-xs-12
          = image_tag image_path(@image_location), class: 'img-fluid'
      .row
        .col-12
          .d-flex.align-items-center.flex-column
            button.btn.btn-primary data-target="#exampleModalCenter" data-toggle="modal" type="button" Share
    = render :partial => 'martiandate/share_modal'
